{
  "doc_id": "23749",
  "text": "We studied 78 patients with de novo AMLs (age, 15-60 years, other than M3) from the GIMEMA (Gruppo Italiano Malattie Ematologiche Maligne dell'Adulto) LAM 99P and GIMEMA/EORTC (European Organization for Research on Treatment of Cancer) AML12 trials, showing greater than 70% bone marrow infiltration by leukemic cells, previously characterized for subcellular NPM localization, karyotype, reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) for major fusion transcripts, MLL status, FLT3 mutations. [CITATION_1] NPM subcellular localization was detected in bone marrow paraffin sections 4 using specific anti-NPM monoclonal antibodies [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] and the alkaline phosphatase anti-alkaline phosphatase technique. [CITATION_4] NPM mutations were previously reported in 24 of 78 of cases. [CITATION_5] Additional mutational analysis of NPM transcript was performed by PCR amplification of cDNA with the following primers: 5Ј-region, Fw1, 5Ј-GGTTGTTCTCTGGAGCAGCGTTCT-3Ј, and Rev1, 5Ј-GGAGTATCTCG-TATAGATTTCTTCAC-3Ј; 3Ј-region, Fw2, 5Ј-GGAGGAGGATGTGAA-ACTCTTAAG-3Ј, and Rev2, 5Ј-ACTGCCAGATATCAACTGTTACAG-3Ј.",
